#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kubrick; is based on the famous <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Rubik%27s_Cube\"><trademark>Rubik's Cube</trademark> </ulink> puzzle, "
"invented by <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ern%C5%91_Rubik"
"\">Professor Ern&odblac; Rubik</ulink> in Hungary in the 1970s. His original "
"puzzle was a cube that appeared to consist of 27 smaller colored cubes, "
"called <quote>cubies</quote>, arranged in a 3x3x3 stack. When you turned the "
"faces of the cube, the colors of the cubies became shuffled and the "
"challenge was to unshuffle them, so that each face of the cube contained a "
"single color."
msgstr ""
"&kubrick; temelji na znani uganki <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Rubik%27s_Cube\"><trademark>Rubikove kocke</trademark> </ulink>, ki jo je "
"izumil <ulink url=\"https ://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ern%C5%91_Rubik"
"\">Profesor Ern&odblac; Rubik</ulink> na Madžarskem v sedemdesetih letih "
"prejšnjega stoletja. Njegova prvotna uganka je bila kocka, za katero se je "
"zdelo, da je sestavljena iz 27 manjših barvnih kock, imenovanih "
"<quote>kockice</quote>, razporejenih v kup 3x3x3. Ko ste obrnili ploskve "
"kocke, so se barve kock premešale in izziv je bil, kako jih premešati, tako "
"da je vsaka ploskev kocke vsebovala eno barvo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &kubrick; the cube sizes range from 2x2x2 (easy) up to 6x6x6 (very hard), "
"or you can play with irregular <quote>bricks</quote> such as 5x3x2 and "
"<quote>mats</quote> (one cubie thick) such as 6x4x1. The game has a "
"selection of puzzles at several levels of difficulty, as well as some "
"demonstrations of pretty patterns and solution moves. It is also possible to "
"make up your own puzzles."
msgstr ""
"V &kubrick; se velikosti kock gibljejo od 2x2x2 (lahko) do 6x6x6 (zelo "
"težko) ali pa se lahko igrate z nepravilnimi <quote>kockami</quote>, kot je "
"5x3x2, in <quote>podlogami</quote> (debelina ene kocke), kot je npr. 6x4x1. "
"Igra ima izbor ugank na več težavnostnih ravneh, pa tudi nekaj predstavitev "
"lepih vzorcev in potez rešitve. Možno je tudi sestavljanje lastnih ugank."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:143
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to Play"
msgstr "Kako igrati"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid "Objective:"
msgstr "Cilj:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Return all the pieces of the cube to their starting positions after the "
"computer has made several shuffling moves."
msgstr ""
"Vrnite vse dele kocke na začetne položaje, potem ko je računalnik izvedel "
"več premešanj."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kubrick; starts with an animated demonstration that randomly chooses cubes "
"of various dimensions, shuffles them and solves them. If you have never seen "
"a <trademark>Rubik's Cube</trademark> before, the demonstration will give "
"you a general idea of how to play. Just click anywhere with the mouse to "
"stop the demonstration and start playing. You will then see a new puzzle or "
"the puzzle you were last working on, exactly as it was when you left it."
msgstr ""
"&kubrick; se začne z animirano demonstracijo, ki naključno izbere kocke "
"različnih dimenzij, jih premeša in reši. Če še nikoli niste videli "
"<trademark>Rubikove kocke</trademark>, vam bo predstavitev dala splošno "
"predstavo o tem, kako igrati. Samo kliknite kjer koli z miško, da ustavite "
"predstavitev in začnete igrati. Nato boste videli novo sestavljanko ali "
"sestavljanko, na kateri ste nazadnje delali, točno tako, kot je bila, ko ste "
"jo zapustili."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kubrick; has a choice of three views, showing one, two or three cubes, all "
"of which are the same cube viewed from different angles. Use the "
"<guimenu>View</guimenu> menu or toolbar buttons to switch between views."
msgstr ""
"&kubrick; ima izbiro med tremi pogledi, ki prikazujejo eno, dve ali tri "
"kocke, ki so vse enake kocke, gledane iz različnih zornih kotov. Za "
"preklapljanje med pogledi uporabite meni <guimenu>Pogled</guimenu> ali gumbe "
"orodne vrstice."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use <menuchoice><guimenu>Game</guimenu><guisubmenu>Choose Puzzle Type</"
"guisubmenu> </menuchoice> menu item to choose the size of cube and degree of "
"difficulty for the type of puzzle you wish to try. Then use "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Game</guimenu> <guimenuitem>New Puzzle</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item each time you wish to re-shuffle the cube and start a "
"new puzzle of that type."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite element menija <menuchoice><guimenu>Igra</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Izberi vrsto uganke</guisubmenu> </menuchoice>, da "
"izberete velikost kocke in stopnjo težavnosti za vrsto uganke, ki jo želite "
"preizkusiti. Nato uporabite element menija <menuchoice><guimenu>Igra</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Nova uganka</guimenuitem></menuchoice> vsakič, ko "
"želite ponovno premešati kocko in začeti novo uganko te vrste."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "Making Moves"
msgstr "Izvajanje premikov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:171
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can use either the mouse or the keyboard to move the cube."
msgstr "Za premikanje kocke lahko uporabite miško ali tipkovnico."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the &LMB; or keyboard to rotate single slices of the cube around any "
"axis, as when solving a puzzle. Square slices (&eg; 4x4 cubies) rotate by 90 "
"degrees at a time. Rectangular slices (&eg; 5x3 cubies) rotate by 180 "
"degrees."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite &LMB; ali tipkovnico za vrtenje posameznih rezin kocke okoli "
"poljubne osi, kot pri reševanju uganke. Kvadratne rezine (&eg; 4x4 kocke) se "
"naenkrat zavrtijo za 90 stopinj. Pravokotne rezine (&eg; 5x3 kocke) se "
"zavrtijo za 180 stopinj."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the &RMB; to rotate the whole cube around any axis. Or use the "
"<keycap>C</keycap> key, within a keyboard sequence. Such moves do not lead "
"to a solution of the puzzle, but you might use them to examine the current "
"position more closely or to get the cube into position for a sequence of "
"solution moves, such as untwisting two corners."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite &RMB; zavrteti celotno kocko okoli poljubne osi. Ali uporabite "
"tipko <keycap>C</keycap> znotraj zaporedja tipkovnice. Takšne poteze ne "
"vodijo do rešitve uganke, lahko pa jih uporabite, da natančneje preučite "
"trenutni položaj ali da postavite kocko v položaj za zaporedje potez "
"rešitve, kot je odvijanje dveh vogalov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All moves, however they are made, are displayed progressively in the toolbar "
"using the widely-recognized Singmaster Notation. See the section <link "
"linkend=\"singmaster-moves\">Singmaster Moves</link> for more details."
msgstr ""
"Vse poteze, ne glede na to, ali so narejene, so postopoma prikazane v orodni "
"vrstici z uporabo splošno priznanega zapisa v Singmaster notaciji. Za več "
"podrobnosti glejte razdelek <link linkend=\"singmaster-moves\">Singmaster "
"premiki</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Mouse to Move"
msgstr "Uporaba miške za premikanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To move using the mouse, click the <mousebutton>left</mousebutton> or &RMB; "
"on any colored sticker on any cubie in the view, hold the button down, drag "
"and let go."
msgstr ""
"Za premikanje z miško kliknite <mousebutton>levo</mousebutton> ali &RMB; na "
"kateri koli barvni nalepki na kateri koli kocki v pogledu pridržite gumb, "
"povlecite in spustite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using the &LMB;, the sticker and a whole slice of the cube will move in "
"the direction you indicated. The slice tilts slightly to help you see what "
"will happen when you let go. If you are not happy with that, just move the "
"mouse back to where you started."
msgstr ""
"Ko uporabljate &LMB;, se nalepka in cela rezina kocke premikata v smeri, ki "
"ste jo navedli. Rezina se rahlo nagne, da vidite, kaj se bo zgodilo, ko jo "
"spustite. Če s tem niste zadovoljni, preprosto premaknite miško nazaj, kjer "
"ste začeli."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:201
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are using the &RMB;, the mouse pointer sticks to the cube and the "
"whole cube rotates with it until you release the button."
msgstr ""
"Če uporabljate &RMB;, se kazalec miške prilepi na kocko in cela kocka se "
"vrti z njim, dokler ne spustite gumba."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:207
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Keyboard to Move"
msgstr "Uporaba tipkovnice za premikanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:209
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two styles of keyboard moves: XYZ moves, described here, and "
"Singmaster moves, which are described in the section <link linkend="
"\"singmaster-moves\">Singmaster Moves</link>."
msgstr ""
"Obstajata dva sloga premikov s tipkovnico: premiki XYZ, opisani tukaj, in "
"premiki Singmaster, ki so opisani v razdelku <link linkend=\"singmaster-moves"
"\">Premiki Singmaster</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To move the cube with XYZ, first use key <keycap>X</keycap>, <keycap>Y</"
"keycap> or <keycap>Z</keycap> to select an axis. On the screen, the X axis "
"runs from left to right, the Y axis from bottom to top and the Z axis "
"towards you from behind the screen. Now, to move the whole cube use key "
"<keycap>C</keycap> or to move a slice use keys <keycap>1</keycap> to "
"<keycap>6</keycap> (to select a slice number)."
msgstr ""
"Če želite premakniti kocko z XYZ, najprej uporabite tipko <keycap>X</"
"keycap>, <keycap>Y</keycap> ali <keycap>Z</keycap>, da izberete os. Na "
"zaslonu poteka os X od leve proti desni, os Y od spodaj navzgor in os Z "
"proti vam izza zaslona. Zdaj, če želite premakniti celotno kocko, uporabite "
"tipko <keycap>C</keycap> ali če želite premakniti rezino, uporabite tipke "
"<keycap>1</keycap> do <keycap>6</keycap> (za izbiro številke rezine)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally use the &Left; arrow key for anti-clockwise rotation and &Right; "
"arrow key for clockwise. The slice that is going to move (numbered 1 to 6) "
"will blink, until you hit an arrow key."
msgstr ""
"Na koncu uporabite &Left; puščično tipko za vrtenje v nasprotni smeri urnega "
"kazalca in &Right; puščična tipka za smer urinega kazalca. Rezina, ki se bo "
"premikala (oštevilčena od 1 do 6), bo utripala, dokler ne pritisnete "
"puščične tipke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can make further moves by using one, two or three of the above keys. For "
"example, to move the same slice again, just hit an arrow key."
msgstr ""
"Nadaljnje poteze lahko izvajate z uporabo ene, dveh ali treh zgornjih tipk. "
"Na primer, če želite znova premakniti isto rezino, pritisnite puščično tipko."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have used the &RMB; to rotate the cube, the meanings of X, Y and Z "
"may have changed, so the cube is automatically realigned, using the "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Move</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Realign Cube</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item, before the keyboard move you have requested can be "
"executed."
msgstr ""
"Če ste uporabili &RMB; za rotacijo kocke so se morda spremenili pomeni X, Y "
"in Z, tako da se kocka samodejno znova poravna z uporabo "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Premakni</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Znova poravnaj kocko</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> element menija, preden se lahko izvede premik "
"tipkovnice, ki ste ga zahtevali."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "Singmaster Moves"
msgstr "Singmaster premiki"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:238
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Professor David Singmaster, an English mathematician, was one of the first "
"to investigate <trademark>Rubik's Cube</trademark> and its relationship to "
"the branch of mathematics known as <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/Group_theory\">Group Theory</ulink>. In his book, <quote>Notes on "
"Rubik's 'Magic Cube'</quote>, Fifth Edition, published in 1980, he sets out "
"a way of describing sequences of cube moves briefly. Mathematicians call "
"this a <quote>notation</quote> and Singmaster's Notation is now widely used "
"internationally in books and on websites when discussing problems and "
"solutions in <trademark>Rubik's Cube</trademark> puzzles. For example, see "
"the Wikipedia article and its links on the subject of <ulink url=\"https://"
"en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rubik%27s_Cube\"><trademark>Rubik's Cube</trademark></"
"ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Profesor David Singmaster, angleški matematik, je bil eden prvih, ki je "
"raziskoval <trademark>Rubikovo kocko</trademark> in njen odnos do veje "
"matematike, znane kot <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Group_theory"
"\">Teorija grup</ulink>. V svoji knjigi <quote>Notes on Rubik's 'Magic "
"Cube'</quote>, peta izdaja, izdani leta 1980, na kratko opiše zaporedje "
"premikanja kocke. Matematiki temu pravijo <quote>notacija</quote> in "
"Singmasterjeva notacija se zdaj široko uporablja po vsem svetu v knjigah in "
"na spletnih mestih, ko se razpravlja o problemih in rešitvah v ugankah "
"<trademark>Rubikove kocke</trademark>. Oglejte si na primer članek v "
"Wikipediji in njegove povezave na temo <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/Rubik%27s_Cube\"><trademark>Rubikova kocka</trademark></ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &kubrick; program uses a modified form of Singmaster Notation to display "
"all moves, by whatever method they are made, using an area of the toolbar. "
"It also allows moves to be entered from the keyboard in Singmaster Notation. "
"The notation has been modified for use on larger cubes, bricks and mats than "
"the original size 3 cube and to allow convenient entry from the keyboard, "
"without clashing with &kubrick; shortcuts or other actions."
msgstr ""
"&kubrick; program uporablja spremenjeno obliko Singmaster notacije za prikaz "
"vseh potez, ne glede na to, na katero metodo so narejene, z uporabo območja "
"orodne vrstice. Omogoča tudi vnos potez s tipkovnice v Singmaster notaciji. "
"Zapis je bil spremenjen za uporabo na večjih kockah, opekah in predlogah od "
"prvotne kocke velikosti 3 in omogoča udoben vnos s tipkovnice, brez "
"navzkrižja z &kubrick; bližnjicami ali drugimi dejanji."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:258
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Briefly, Singmaster imagines that you are looking at the cube from slightly "
"above and to the right of it, exactly as in the standard <guilabel>Front "
"View</guilabel> of &kubrick;. You can see three faces at the top, front and "
"right of the cube and these Singmaster has called (in English) <quote>Up</"
"quote>, <quote>Front</quote> and <quote>Right</quote>, or <command>U</"
"command>, <command>F</command> and <command>R</command> for short. The three "
"faces you cannot see, which are on the <guilabel>Back View</guilabel> in "
"&kubrick;, are at the bottom, back and left of the cube and Singmaster calls "
"these (in English) <quote>Down</quote>, <quote>Back</quote> and <quote>Left</"
"quote>, or <command>D</command>, <command>B</command> and <command>L</"
"command> for short. Singmaster uses <command>U</command> and <command>D</"
"command> for the top and bottom faces because <command>B</command> is "
"reserved for the back face."
msgstr ""
"Na kratko, Singmaster si predstavlja, da gledate kocko nekoliko zgoraj in "
"desno od nje, natanko tako kot v standardnem <guilabel>pogledu od spredaj</"
"guilabel> &kubrick;. Vidite lahko tri ploskve na vrhu, spredaj in desno od "
"kocke, ki jih je Singmaster imenoval (v angleščini) <quote>Up</quote>, "
"<quote>Front</quote> in <quote>Right</quote> ali na kratko <command>U</"
"command>, <command>F</command> in <command>R</command>. Tri ploskve, ki jih "
"ne vidite in so v <guilabel>Pogledu od zadaj</guilabel> v &kubrick;u, so na "
"dnu, zadaj in levo od kocke in Singmaster jih imenuje (v angleščini) "
"<quote>Down</quote >, <quote>Back</quote> in <quote>Left</quote> ali na "
"kratko <command>D</command>, <command>B</command> in <command>L</command>. "
"Singmaster uporablja <command>U</command> in <command>D</command> za zgornjo "
"in spodnjo ploskev, ker je <command>B</command> rezervirana za zadnjo stran."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:271
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is all summarised in the table below: now to the moves. A single letter "
"or keystroke from <command>UFRDBL</command> represents a clockwise move of "
"that face through a right angle (90 degrees) for a square face or through "
"180 degrees for a rectangular face (as on a brick or mat). Here is where it "
"gets tricky."
msgstr ""
"Vse to je povzeto v spodnji tabeli: zdaj pa k potezam. Ena črka ali pritisk "
"tipke iz <command>UFRDBL</command> predstavlja premik te ploskve v smeri "
"urinega kazalca pod pravim kotom (90 stopinj) za kvadratno ploskev ali za "
"180 stopinj za pravokotno ploskev (kot na opeki ali podlogi). Tukaj postane "
"težavno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:278
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Clockwise</quote> means clockwise when you are looking directly at "
"that face. That is easy enough with the <command>UFR</command> faces you can "
"see, but the faces you cannot see appear to move anti-clockwise when you use "
"<command>DBL</command> moves. That is because you are looking at them from "
"behind. On &kubrick;'s <guilabel>Back View</guilabel>, the <command>DBL</"
"command> moves will be seen to go clockwise, as expected. Rather than trying "
"to imagine yourself looking at the back of the cube when making "
"<command>DBL</command> moves, it might be easier to think of them going anti-"
"clockwise in the normal <guilabel>Front View</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"<quote>V smeri urinega kazalca</quote> pomeni v smeri urinega kazalca, ko "
"gledate neposredno v to ploskev. To je dovolj preprosto s ploskvami "
"<command>UFR</command>, ki jih lahko vidite, vendar se zdi, da se ploskve, "
"ki jih ne vidite, premikajo v nasprotni smeri urinega kazalca, ko "
"uporabljate premike <command>DBL</command>. To je zato, ker jih gledate od "
"zadaj. V &kubrick; <guilabel>Pogledu od zadaj</guilabel> bodo prikazani "
"premiki <command>DBL</command> v smeri urinega kazalca, kot je pričakovano. "
"Namesto da si poskušate predstavljati, kako gledate zadnji del kocke, ko "
"izvajate poteze <command>DBL</command>, bi bilo morda lažje razmišljati, da "
"gredo v nasprotni smeri urinega kazalca v običajnem <guilabel>pogledu od "
"spredaj</guilabel>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "Singmaster Notation (Modified)"
msgstr "Singmaster notacija (spremenjena)"

#. Tag: segtitle
#: index.docbook:291
#, no-c-format
msgid "<segtitle>Key</segtitle>"
msgstr "<segtitle>Ključ</segtitle>"

#. Tag: segtitle
#: index.docbook:291
#, no-c-format
msgid "Meaning"
msgstr "Pomen"

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:292
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Right face. In English, <command>R</command> is for <quote>Right</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Desna ploskev. V angleščini je <command>R</command> za <quote>Right</quote>."

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:294
#, no-c-format
msgid "Left face. In English, <command>L</command> is for <quote>Left</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Leva ploskev. V angleščini je <command>L</command> za <quote>Left</quote>."

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Up or top face. In English, <command>U</command> is for <quote>Up</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Gor ali zgornja ploskev. V angleščini je <command>U</command> za <quote>Up</"
"quote>."

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:298
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Down or bottom face. In English, <command>D</command> is for <quote>Down</"
"quote>."
msgstr ""
"Dol ali spodnja ploskev. V angleščini <command>D</command> pomeni "
"<quote>Down</quote>."

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:300
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Front face. In English, <command>F</command> is for <quote>Front</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Sprednja ploskev. V angleščini je <command>F</command> za <quote>Front</"
"quote>."

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:302
#, no-c-format
msgid "Back face. In English, <command>B</command> is for <quote>Back</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Zadnja ploskev. V angleščini je <command>B</command> za <quote>Back</quote>."

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Suffix for a reverse or anti-clockwise move. <command>R'</command> is the "
"reverse of <command>R</command>."
msgstr ""
"Pripona za vzvratni premik ali premik v nasprotni smeri urinega kazalca. "
"<command>R'</command> je obratno od <command>R</command>."

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:306
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Suffix for double move. <command>R2</command> rotates <command>R</command> "
"twice."
msgstr ""
"Pripona za dvojno premikanje. <command>R2</command> dvakrat zavrti "
"<command>R</command>."

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:308
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Suffix for two-face move. <command>R+</command> is <command>RL'</command> in "
"another form."
msgstr ""
"Pripona za dvostransko potezo. <command>R+</command> je <command>RL'</"
"command> v drugi obliki."

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:310
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Suffix for anti-two-face move. <command>R-</command> is <command>RL</"
"command> in another form."
msgstr ""
"Pripona proti potezi z dvema ploskvama. <command>R-</command> je "
"<command>RL</command> v drugi obliki."

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Prefix for inner-slice move. <command>.R</command> is one step in from the "
"<command>R</command> face."
msgstr ""
"Predpona za premik notranje rezine. <command>.R</command> je en korak od "
"ploskve <command>R</command>."

#. Tag: seg
#: index.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Prefix for whole-cube move. In English, <command>C</command> is for "
"<quote>Cube</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Predpona za premik cele kocke. V angleščini je <command>C</command> za "
"<quote>Cube</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:319
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Singmaster uses a letter followed by an apostrophe to represent an anti-"
"clockwise or reverse move of a face. Mathematicians would say <command>F'</"
"command> as <quote>F prime</quote> or <quote>F dash</quote> and it indicates "
"an anti-clockwise move of the front face."
msgstr ""
"Singmaster uporablja črko, ki ji sledi apostrof, da predstavlja premik "
"ploskve v nasprotni smeri urinega kazalca ali obratno. Matematiki bi rekli "
"<command>F'</command> kot <quote>F prime</quote> ali <quote>F pomišljaj</"
"quote> in označuje premik sprednje ploskve v nasprotni smeri urnega kazalca."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kubrick; cannot tell if you are going to type an apostrophe, another letter "
"or some other symbol after a letter, so it will not make a clockwise move of "
"a face immediately after you type the letter. You can force &kubrick; to "
"move by hitting the &Enter; or <keycap>Return</keycap> key. You can also use "
"the &Space; bar and it will leave a space in the display of moves, allowing "
"you to separate groups of moves for readability."
msgstr ""
"&kubrick; ne more vedeti, ali boste za črko vnesli apostrof, drugo črko ali "
"kakšen drug simbol, zato ne bo premaknil ploskve v smeri urinega kazalca "
"takoj, ko vnesete črko. Lahko vsilite &kubrick; za premikanje s pritiskom na "
"&Enter; ali tipko <keycap>Return</keycap>. Uporabite lahko tudi &Space; "
"vrstico in pustil bo prostor v prikazu potez, kar vam bo omogočilo ločevanje "
"skupin potez za berljivost."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On cubes, bricks or mats of size 3 or more, you might wish to move an inner "
"slice, rather than a face. To do this, type one or more periods or dots "
"before the face letter. For example, <command>..F</command> moves the slice "
"that is two layers behind the front face and <command>..B</command> would "
"move the slice two layers in front of the back face, assuming there are 5 or "
"6 layers that can move. The reverse of those moves would be <command>..F'</"
"command> and <command>..B'</command>."
msgstr ""
"Na kockah, opekah ali podlogah velikosti 3 ali več boste morda želeli "
"premakniti notranjo rezino namesto ploskve. Če želite to narediti, vnesite "
"eno ali več pik ali pik pred črko ploskve. Na primer, <command>..F</command> "
"premakne rezino, ki je dve plasti za sprednjo ploskev, <command>..B</"
"command> pa bi premaknil rezino dve plasti pred zadnjo ploskev, ob "
"predpostavki, da tam je 5 ali 6 plasti, ki se lahko premikajo. Obratno od "
"teh potez bi bilo <command>..F'</command> in <command>..B'</command>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally, the <command>C</command> prefix moves the whole cube in the same "
"way as a face. For example, <command>CF</command> moves the cube clockwise "
"along with the front face and <command>CF'</command> moves it anti-clockwise."
msgstr ""
"Nazadnje, predpona <command>C</command> premakne celotno kocko na enak način "
"kot ploskev. Na primer, <command>CF</command> premakne kocko v smeri urinega "
"kazalca skupaj s sprednjo ploskvijo in <command>CF'</command> jo premakne v "
"nasprotni smeri urinega kazalca."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:343
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have previously rotated the cube by hand, using the &RMB;, and you "
"then make a Singmaster or other keyboard move, the cube will be realigned "
"automatically to standard <command>UFR</command> view and some <command>C</"
"command> moves will be generated and displayed. This ensures that you and "
"&kubrick; have the same idea of top, front and right. Similar moves are "
"generated when you use the <menuchoice><guimenu>Move</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Realign Cube</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item or the "
"<guiicon>Realign Cube</guiicon> icon on the toolbar."
msgstr ""
"Če ste kocko pred tem zavrteli ročno z uporabo &RMB;, nato pa izvedete "
"premik s Singmasterjem ali drugo tipkovnico, bo kocka samodejno ponovno "
"poravnana v standardnem pogledu <command>UFR</command> in nekaj <command>C</"
"command> bodo ustvarjeni in prikazani premiki. To zagotavlja, da boste vi in "
"&kubrick; imela enako predstavo o vrhu, spredaj in desno. Podobni premiki se "
"ustvarijo, ko uporabite element menija <menuchoice><guimenu>Premakni</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Znova poravnaj kocko</guimenuitem></menuchoice> ali "
"ikono <guiicon>Znova poravnaj kocko</guiicon> v orodni vrstici."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:354
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Rules, Strategies and Tips"
msgstr "Pravila igre, strategije in nasveti"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rules"
msgstr "Pravila"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:359
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are no rules in &kubrick; other than having to move one slice at a "
"time until all the cubies and their stickers are back in their original "
"positions. No other rules are necessary, because the way the cube is built "
"makes it almost impossible to perform any other moves."
msgstr ""
"V &kubrick; ni pravil. razen tega, da morate premikati po eno rezino "
"naenkrat, dokler se vse kocke in njihove nalepke ne vrnejo na svoje prvotne "
"položaje. Nobena druga pravila niso potrebna, saj način, kako je kocka "
"zgrajena, skoraj onemogoča izvajanje drugih potez."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the original 3x3x3 <trademark>Rubik's Cube</trademark>, the inside of the "
"cube contained an ingenious mechanism that made it possible to turn groups "
"of 9 cubies (3x3) called <quote>slices</quote>, all at once as a group. To "
"make any other moves you had to physically break the cube or take it apart "
"and re-assemble it. The equivalent in &kubrick; would be to change the "
"source program."
msgstr ""
"V originalni 3x3x3 <trademark>Rubikovi kocki</trademark> je notranjost kocke "
"vsebovala domiseln mehanizem, ki je omogočal obračanje skupin 9 kock (3x3), "
"imenovanih <quote>rezine</quote>, vse naenkrat kot skupina. Za izvedbo "
"kakršnih koli drugih potez ste morali fizično razbiti kocko ali jo "
"razstaviti in ponovno sestaviti. Ekvivalent v &kubrick; bi bilo spremeniti "
"izvorni program."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:373
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Complexity of the Puzzle"
msgstr "Kompleksnost uganke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:375
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The outside faces of the cubies have stickers of 6 different colors, one for "
"each of the 6 faces of the main cube. As you rotate the slices, the stickers "
"become shuffled and the faces of the main cube become a jumble of colors. It "
"looks like a simple puzzle, but as you move further away from the starting "
"position, you begin to realise, as one writer put it, that you are like a "
"small child who has let go of a helium balloon only to see it move more and "
"more beyond reach or hope of return."
msgstr ""
"Zunanje ploskve kock imajo nalepke 6 različnih barv, eno za vsako od 6 "
"ploskev glavne kocke. Ko vrtite rezine, se nalepke premešajo in ploskve "
"glavne kocke postanejo mešanica barv. Videti je kot preprosta uganka, toda "
"ko se bolj odmikate od začetnega položaja, se začnete zavedati, kot je rekel "
"neki pisec, da ste kot majhen otrok, ki je spustil helijev balon samo zato, "
"da bi videl, kako se premika še bolj in več nedosegljivo ali brez upanja na "
"vrnitev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Mathematicians calculate that a 3x3x3 cube can be shuffled into "
"43,252,003,274,489,856,000 different patterns, yet they conjecture that all "
"positions can be solved in 20 moves or less. The method that can do that (as "
"yet undiscovered) is called <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/God"
"%27s_algorithm\">God's Algorithm</ulink>. Practical methods can take more "
"than 100 moves. As there are 12 face-move possibilities at each step, the "
"chances of solving the cube by trial and error are rather remote. Some cubes "
"have 9-part pictures on the faces and that makes them even more complex, "
"because you then have to get the orientations of the stickers correct as "
"well as the positions."
msgstr ""
"Matematiki izračunajo, da je kocko 3x3x3 mogoče premešati v "
"43.252.003.274.489.856.000 različnih vzorcev, vendar domnevajo, da je vse "
"položaje mogoče rešiti v 20 potezah ali manj. Metoda, ki to lahko naredi (še "
"neodkrita), se imenuje <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/God"
"%27s_algorithm\">Božji algoritem</ulink>. Praktične metode lahko zahtevajo "
"več kot 100 potez. Ker je na vsakem koraku na voljo 12 možnosti premika "
"ploskev, so možnosti za rešitev kocke s poskusi in napakami precej majhne. "
"Nekatere kocke imajo na ploskvah 9-delne slike, zaradi česar so še bolj "
"zapletene, saj morate potem pravilno usmeriti nalepke in položaje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:397
#, no-c-format
msgid "Strategies and Tips"
msgstr "Strategije in nasveti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:399
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kubrick; shuffles the cube by a pre-selected number of random moves when "
"setting a puzzle. The difficulty depends on how many cubies there are in "
"your cube, how many shuffling moves there are and whether you can view the "
"shuffling moves as they happen."
msgstr ""
"&kubrick; pri postavljanju uganke premeša kocko za vnaprej izbrano število "
"naključnih potez. Težavnost je odvisna od tega, koliko kock je v vaši kocki, "
"koliko premešanih potez je in ali si lahko ogledate premešane poteze, ko se "
"zgodijo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:404
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One kind of puzzle has a small number of shuffling moves (3, 4 or 5) and the "
"idea is to solve the cube in that number of moves (or less). This is fun, "
"challenging and quite quick to play."
msgstr ""
"Ena vrsta uganke ima majhno število potez (3, 4 ali 5) in ideja je rešiti "
"kocko v tem številu potez (ali manj). To je zabavno, zahtevno in precej "
"hitro za igranje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:408
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then there is the traditional puzzle, with 10 to 20 or more shuffling moves. "
"The 3x3x3 cube has been very well explored and written about, but other "
"sizes are not so well known and understood."
msgstr ""
"Potem je tu še tradicionalna uganka z 10 do 20 ali več premešanimi potezami. "
"Kocka 3x3x3 je bila zelo dobro raziskana in o njej napisano, druge velikosti "
"pa niso tako dobro poznane in razumljene."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:412
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kubrick; also has bricks and mats you can play with. Some of them are "
"easier to solve than cubes and could be fun for children too."
msgstr ""
"&kubrick; ima tudi kocke in podloge, s katerimi se lahko igrate. Nekatere "
"izmed njih je lažje rešiti kot kocke in bi lahko bile zabavne tudi za otroke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:415
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another game you can try is to find pretty patterns for sizes other than "
"3x3x3."
msgstr ""
"Druga igra, ki jo lahko poskusite, je iskanje lepih vzorcev za velikosti, ki "
"niso 3x3x3."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:418
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kubrick; can be used as a <quote>laboratory</quote> for studying cubes and "
"finding sequences of solution moves, since all moves can be undone or redone "
"to any degree, either instantaneously or at a selectable speed of animation."
msgstr ""
"&kubrick; se lahko uporablja kot <quote>laboratorij</quote> za preučevanje "
"kock in iskanje zaporedij potez rešitev, saj je vse poteze mogoče "
"razveljaviti ali ponovno izvesti do poljubne stopnje, bodisi takoj ali z "
"izbrano hitrostjo animacije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:423
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also possible to save and restore a partly solved cube at any time and "
"the current state of the cube is automatically saved and restored when you "
"quit and restart &kubrick;."
msgstr ""
"Prav tako je mogoče kadar koli shraniti in obnoviti delno rešeno kocko, "
"trenutno stanje kocke pa se samodejno shrani in obnovi, ko zaprete in znova "
"zaženete &kubrick;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On a cube with an odd number of cubies per face, the stickers at the centres "
"of the six faces maintain their positions relative to each other, regardless "
"of how you move. You can use those centres as anchors or guide posts for "
"your moves."
msgstr ""
"Na kocki z lihim številom kock na ploskev nalepke v središčih šestih ploskev "
"ohranijo svoj položaj glede na drugo, ne glede na to, kako se premikate. Ta "
"središča lahko uporabite kot sidra ali vodilne stebre za svoje poteze."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:432
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> menu has options to turn animations on or "
"off and to vary the speed of animations. These can be useful when trying to "
"follow a sequence of moves and understand what is happening."
msgstr ""
"Meni <guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> ima možnosti za vklop ali izklop animacij "
"in spreminjanje hitrosti animacij. To je lahko koristno, ko poskušate "
"slediti zaporedju potez in razumeti, kaj se dogaja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:436
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are in real trouble, &kubrick; has a <quote>solve</quote> action "
"which appears to show God's Algorithm in animated form then reshuffles the "
"cube. Actually the computer cheats. It remembers the shuffling moves and "
"then just undoes and redoes them."
msgstr ""
"Če ste v resnih težavah, &kubrick; ima dejanje <quote>reši</quote>, ki "
"prikazuje Božji algoritem v animirani obliki, nato pa premeša kocko. "
"Pravzaprav računalnik goljufa. Zapomni si premešane poteze in jih nato samo "
"razveljavi in ponovi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:441
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another source of ideas is the <menuchoice><guimenu>Demos</guimenu> "
"<guisubmenu>Solution Moves</guisubmenu></menuchoice> menu item. One "
"systematic way to solve a cube is to solve the bottom layer first, then the "
"edge cubies in the middle layer and finally the top layer. The demos show "
"sequences of moves on the 3x3x3 cube that will rearrange a few cubies at a "
"time, without messing up parts of the cube you have already solved. One of "
"the demos plays a complete solution of an example cube, using these methods, "
"but it requires over 100 moves."
msgstr ""
"Drug vir idej je menijski element <menuchoice><guimenu>Demos</guimenu> "
"<guisubmenu>Premiki rešitve</guisubmenu></menuchoice>. Eden od sistematičnih "
"načinov za reševanje kocke je, da najprej rešite spodnjo plast, nato robne "
"kocke v srednji plasti in nazadnje zgornjo plast. Predstavitve prikazujejo "
"zaporedja potez na kocki 3x3x3, ki bodo prerazporedile nekaj kock naenkrat, "
"ne da bi pokvarili dele kocke, ki ste jih že rešili. Ena od predstavitev "
"predvaja popolno rešitev vzorčne kocke z uporabo teh metod, vendar zahteva "
"več kot 100 potez."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "Interface Overview"
msgstr "Pregled vmesnika"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:457
#, no-c-format
msgid "Menu Items"
msgstr "Elementi menija"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<menuchoice> <shortcut><keycap>N</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Game</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>New Puzzle</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> <menuchoice> "
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut><guimenu></guimenu> </menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"<menuchoice> <shortcut><keycap>N</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Nova uganka</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> <menuchoice> "
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut><guimenu></guimenu> </menuchoice>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:469
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generate a new puzzle of the type currently selected."
msgstr "Ustvarite novo sestavljanko trenutno izbrane vrste."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:474
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>O</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Load Puzzle…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>O</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Naloži uganko...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:479
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Load a previously saved puzzle, with all of its dimensions, settings, "
"current state of the cube and history of moves, using a file selection "
"dialog box to locate the required file."
msgstr ""
"Naložite predhodno shranjeno sestavljanko z vsemi njenimi dimenzijami, "
"nastavitvami, trenutnim stanjem kocke in zgodovino premikov, pri čemer "
"uporabite pogovorno okno za izbiro datoteke, da poiščete želeno datoteko."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:486
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Shift;<keycap>U</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Restart Puzzle…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Shift;<keycap>U</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ponovni zagon uganke...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:491 index.docbook:582
#, no-c-format
msgid "Undo all previous moves and start again."
msgstr "Razveljavi vse prejšnje poteze in začni znova."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:496
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Save Puzzle…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Shrani uganko...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:501
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save the current puzzle, with all of its dimensions, settings, current state "
"of the cube and history of moves, using a file selection dialog box to name "
"a new file if the puzzle has not previously been saved and loaded."
msgstr ""
"Shranite trenutno uganko z vsemi njenimi dimenzijami, nastavitvami, "
"trenutnim stanjem kocke in zgodovino premikov, pri čemer uporabite pogovorno "
"okno za izbiro datoteke, da poimenujete novo datoteko, če uganka še ni bila "
"shranjena in naložena."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:509
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Save Puzzle As…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Shrani uganko kot...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:512
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save the current puzzle under a new file name, with all of its dimensions, "
"settings, current state of the cube and history of moves, using a file "
"selection dialog box."
msgstr ""
"Shranite trenutno sestavljanko pod novim imenom datoteke z vsemi "
"dimenzijami, nastavitvami, trenutnim stanjem kocke in zgodovino premikov s "
"pogovornim oknom za izbiro datoteke."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:519
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Game</guimenu><guisubmenu>Choose Puzzle Type</guisubmenu>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guisubmenu>Izberi vrsto uganke</guisubmenu>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:522
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose a type of puzzle to play from a series of sub-menus graded by "
"difficulty, based on cube dimensions and number of shuffling moves, or use "
"sub-menu item <guimenuitem>Make Your Own…</guimenuitem> to create your own "
"puzzle, using a dialog box."
msgstr ""
"Izberite vrsto uganke, ki jo želite igrati, iz niza podmenijev, razvrščenih "
"po težavnosti na podlagi dimenzij kocke in števila premešanih potez, ali pa "
"uporabite element podmenija <guimenuitem>Izdelajte svojo lastno...</"
"guimenuitem>, da ustvarite svojo lastno uganko z uporabo pogovornega okna."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:530
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Q</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Quit</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Q</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Zapusti</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:535
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Quit</action> &kubrick;, automatically saving the current puzzle's "
"dimensions, settings, state of the cube and history of moves."
msgstr ""
"<action>Zapusti</action> &kubrick;, samodejno shrani dimenzije trenutne "
"uganke, nastavitve, stanje kocke in zgodovino potez."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:541
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Z</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Move</guimenu><guimenuitem>Undo</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Z</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</guimenu><guimenuitem>Razveljavi</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:545
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Undo a previous move</action> (repeatedly if required)."
msgstr "<action>Razveljavi prejšnji premik</action> (po potrebi večkrat)."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:549
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>Z</keycap></"
"keycombo> </shortcut> <guimenu>Move</guimenu><guimenuitem>Redo</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>Z</keycap></"
"keycombo> </shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ponovi</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:553
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Redo a previously undone move</action> (repeatedly if required)."
msgstr ""
"<action>Ponovi predhodno razveljavljeno potezo</action> (po potrebi večkrat)."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:558
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>D</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Move</guimenu><guimenuitem>Main Demo</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>D</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</guimenu><guimenuitem>Glavna predstavitev</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:562
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Start/Stop demo of random puzzle solving</action> on the start page "
"of &kubrick;."
msgstr ""
"<action>Začni/ustavi predstavitev naključnega reševanja ugank</action> na "
"začetni strani &kubrick;."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:567
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycap>S</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Move</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Solve</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycap>S</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Reši</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:569
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Solve the cube.</action> This shows all your moves being undone, "
"then all the shuffling moves being undone and then the shuffling moves being "
"re-done, leaving you set up to have another go at the puzzle."
msgstr ""
"<action>Reši kocko.</action> To kaže, da so bile vse vaše poteze "
"razveljavljene, nato vse poteze mešanja, ki so bile razveljavljene, nato pa "
"so poteze mešanja ponovno izvedene, tako da ste nastavljeni, da se znova "
"lotite uganke."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:576
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut> <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Shift;<keycap>U</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Move</guimenu><guimenuitem>Restart Puzzle</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut> <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Shift;<keycap>U</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</guimenu><guimenuitem>Znova zaženi uganko</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:587
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut> <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Shift;<keycap>R</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Move</guimenu><guimenuitem>Redo All</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut> <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Shift;<keycap>R</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ponovi vse</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:592
#, no-c-format
msgid "Redo all previously undone moves."
msgstr "Ponovite vse prej razveljavljene poteze."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:596
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycap>Home</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Move</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Realign Cube</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycap>Domov</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Znova poravnaj kocko</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:599
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Adjust the orientation of a rotated cube by the minimum amount "
"needed to make the rotations a combination of 90 degree moves</action>, thus "
"setting the axes parallel to the XYZ axes. In addition, some whole-cube 90 "
"degree moves are inserted in your list of moves to achieve the desired "
"effect."
msgstr ""
"<action>Prilagodite orientacijo zasukane kocke za najmanjšo količino, ki je "
"potrebna, da postanejo vrtenja kombinacija premikov za 90 stopinj</action>, "
"s čimer nastavite osi, vzporedne z osmi XYZ. Poleg tega je nekaj premikov "
"celotne kocke za 90 stopinj vstavljenih na vaš seznam premikov, da dosežete "
"želeni učinek."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:605
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is to standardise the view's perspective so that the top, front and "
"right sides are visible together and keyboard moves become properly "
"meaningful. The inserted moves can be undone and redone, exactly as if you "
"had made them directly yourself."
msgstr ""
"To je namenjeno standardizaciji perspektive pogleda, tako da so zgornja, "
"sprednja in desna stran vidne skupaj, premiki tipkovnice pa postanejo "
"pravilno smiselni. Vstavljene poteze je mogoče razveljaviti in ponoviti, "
"natanko tako, kot če bi jih naredili sami."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:610
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, if you have used the &RMB; to turn the cube upside-down, the "
"top or Up (<command>U</command>) face is now what used to be the bottom or "
"Down (<command>D</command>) face and what used to be the Y axis is pointing "
"downwards. In this situation, <menuchoice><guimenu>Move</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Realign Cube</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item will redefine "
"the faces and axes so that the new top face is known as Up (<command>U</"
"command>) and the Y axis is again the one that points upwards."
msgstr ""
"Na primer, če ste uporabili &RMB; če kocko obrnete na glavo, je zgornja ali "
"gornja (<command>U</command>) ploskev zdaj tisto, kar je bila spodnja ali "
"dol (<command>D</command>) stran in kar je bila Y os je obrnjena navzdol. V "
"tem primeru menijski element <menuchoice><guimenu>Premakni</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Znova poravnaj kocko</guimenuitem></menuchoice> na novo "
"definira ploskve in osi, tako da bo nova zgornja ploskev znana kot Gor "
"(<command>U</command>) in os Y je spet tista, ki kaže navzgor."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:620
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>1 Cube</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>1 kocka</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:623
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show a view of the front of the cube."
msgstr "Pokažite pogled na sprednjo stran kocke."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:627
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>2 Cubes</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>2 kocki</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:630
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Show views of the front and back of the cube.</action> Slice moves "
"and rotations can be performed on either picture and the other will move "
"simultaneously."
msgstr ""
"<action>Pokaži pogled na sprednji in zadnji del kocke.</action> Premike "
"rezin in rotacije je mogoče izvajati na kateri koli sliki, druga pa se bo "
"premikala sočasno."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:636
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>3 Cubes</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>3 kocke</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:639
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Show a large view of the front of the cube and two smaller views of "
"the front and back.</action> Slice moves can be performed on any of the "
"pictures and the others will move simultaneously, but only the large one can "
"be rotated."
msgstr ""
"<action>Prikaži velik pogled na sprednji del kocke in dva manjša pogleda na "
"sprednji in zadnji del.</action> Premike rezin je mogoče izvajati na kateri "
"koli sliki, druge pa se bodo premikale hkrati, vendar se lahko samo velika "
"da vrteti."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:646
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>D</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Demos</guimenu><guimenuitem>Main Demo</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>D</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Predstavitve</guimenu><guimenuitem>Glavna predstavitev</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:651
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Run the Main Demo</action>, in which a cube changes shape, shuffles "
"and solves itself as it rotates at random."
msgstr ""
"<action>Zaženi glavno predstavitev</action>, v kateri kocka spreminja "
"obliko, se meša in rešuje, ko se naključno vrti."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:656
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Demos</guimenu><guisubmenu>Pretty Patterns</guisubmenu>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Predstavitve</guimenu><guisubmenu>Lepi vzorci</guisubmenu>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Show a sub-menu in which pretty patterns on the 3x3x3 cube can be "
"selected and the moves to create them are demonstrated.</action> There is "
"also an <guimenuitem>Info</guimenuitem> item that tells you a little more "
"about such patterns."
msgstr ""
"<action>Pokaži podmeni, v katerem je mogoče izbrati lepe vzorce na kocki "
"3x3x3 in prikazati poteze za njihovo ustvarjanje.</action> Obstaja tudi "
"element <guimenuitem>Informacije</guimenuitem>, ki vam pove nekaj malega več "
"o takih vzorcih."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:666
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Demos</guimenu><guisubmenu>Solution Moves</guisubmenu>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Predstavitve</guimenu><guisubmenu>Premiki rešitve</guisubmenu>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:669
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Show a sub-menu in which sequences of moves used to solve the 3x3x3 "
"cube can be selected and the sequences are demonstrated.</action> There is "
"also an <guimenuitem>Info</guimenuitem> item that tells you a little more "
"about such solution moves."
msgstr ""
"<action>Pokaži podmeni, v katerem je mogoče izbrati zaporedja potez, "
"uporabljenih za reševanje kocke 3x3x3, in prikazati zaporedja.</action> "
"Obstaja tudi element <guimenuitem>Informacije</guimenuitem>, ki vam pove "
"nekaj malega več o tovrstnih potezah rešitev."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:676
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycap>W</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Watch Shuffling</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycap>W</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Gledanje premetavanja</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:679
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Show animations of shuffling moves as they occur.</action> This is "
"an aid for beginners, but might be a form of cheating for experienced "
"players."
msgstr ""
"<action>Prikaži animacije premešanih potez, ko se zgodijo.</action> To je "
"pomoč za začetnike, vendar je lahko oblika goljufanja za izkušene igralce."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycap>O</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Watch Your Own Moves</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycap>O</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Pazi na lastne poteze</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:688
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Show animations of your own moves as they occur.</action> This is an "
"aid for beginners, because it slows down the animations. Experienced players "
"can turn this option off and moves are then animated at high speed, taking "
"about a tenth of a second to turn 90 degrees."
msgstr ""
"<action>Pokaži animacije lastnih potez, ko se zgodijo.</action> To je pomoč "
"za začetnike, ker upočasni animacije. Izkušeni igralci lahko to možnost "
"izklopijo in poteze se nato animirajo z veliko hitrostjo, za obrat za 90 "
"stopinj pa potrebuje približno desetinko sekunde."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:696
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure Toolbars…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj orodne vrstice...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:699
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Open a dialog where you can configure the toolbar actions</action> "
"for &kubrick;."
msgstr ""
"<action>Odprite pogovorno okno, kjer lahko konfigurirate dejanja orodne "
"vrstice</action> za &kubrick;."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:704
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>&kubrick; Game Settings</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu><guimenuitem>&kubrick; Nastavitve igre</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:707
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Open a game settings dialog.</action> See <link linkend="
"\"configuration\">Game Configuration</link> section for more details."
msgstr ""
"<action>Odprite pogovorno okno z nastavitvami igre.</action> Za več "
"podrobnosti glejte razdelek <link linkend=\"configuration\">Konfiguracija "
"igre</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Additionally &kubrick; has the common &kde; <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> and "
"<guimenu>Help</guimenu> menu items, for more information read the sections "
"about the <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-settings"
"\">Settings Menu</ulink> and <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus."
"html#menus-help\">Help Menu</ulink> of the &kde; Fundamentals."
msgstr ""
"Poleg tega &kubrick; ima skupno &kde; Elemente menija <guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu> in <guimenu>Pomoč</guimenu>, za več informacij preberite razdelke o "
"<ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-settings\">meniju z "
"nastavitvami</ulink> in <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-help"
"\">meni Pomoč</ulink> v &kde; Osnove."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:725
#, no-c-format
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr "Pogosto zastavljena vprašanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:732
#, no-c-format
msgid "How do I pause the game?"
msgstr "Kako ustavim igro?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:733
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kubrick; does not have a <quote>Pause</quote> feature, because none is "
"required. If a demo is running, just click anywhere to stop it."
msgstr ""
"&kubrick; nima funkcije <quote>Premor</quote>, ker ni potrebna. Če se demo "
"izvaja, samo kliknite kjer koli, da ga ustavite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:739
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can I change the way this game looks?"
msgstr "Ali lahko spremenim videz te igre?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:740
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Currently you can change the view, using the <guimenu>View </guimenu> menu, "
"the amount and speed of animation and the bevel on the edges of the cubies, "
"using the <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> menu."
msgstr ""
"Trenutno lahko spremenite pogled z uporabo menija <guimenu>Pogled </"
"guimenu>, količino in hitrost animacije ter poševnino na robovih kock z "
"uporabo menija <guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:746
#, no-c-format
msgid "I have made a mistake. Can I undo?"
msgstr "Naredil sem napako. Ali lahko razveljavim?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:747
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Yes. This is one of the strengths of &kubrick; as compared to a real puzzle. "
"You can undo and redo moves to any level, or undo all moves and start again. "
"To undo and redo moves, use the <guimenu>Move</guimenu> menu or the "
"corresponding keyboard shortcuts and toolbar buttons."
msgstr ""
"Da. To je ena od prednosti &kubrick; v primerjavi s pravo uganko. Lahko "
"razveljavite in ponovite poteze na kateri koli ravni ali pa razveljavite vse "
"poteze in začnete znova. Če želite razveljaviti in ponoviti poteze, "
"uporabite meni <guimenu>Premakni</guimenu> ali ustrezne bližnjice na "
"tipkovnici in gumbe v orodni vrstici."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:756
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can I use the keyboard to play this game?"
msgstr "Ali lahko uporabljam tipkovnico za igranje te igre?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:757
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Yes. &kubrick; has keyboard moves based on the X, Y and Z axes and others "
"based on <link linkend=\"singmaster-moves\">Singmaster notation</link>, "
"which uses one-letter abbreviations for Front, Back, Left, Right, Up and "
"Down faces of the cube."
msgstr ""
"Da. &kubrick; ima premike s tipkovnico na podlagi osi X, Y in Z ter druge na "
"podlagi <link linkend=\"singmaster-moves\">Singmaster notacije</link>, ki "
"uporablja enočrkovne okrajšave za spredaj, zadaj, levo, desno, gor in "
"spodnje ploskve kocke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:764
#, no-c-format
msgid "I cannot figure out what to do here! Are there hints?"
msgstr "Ne morem ugotoviti, kaj naj naredim tukaj! Ali obstajajo namigi?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:766
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"No. However, the 3x3x3 <trademark>Rubik's Cube</trademark> has been "
"extensively analysed and you can find solution methods on the Internet and "
"in menu item <menuchoice><guimenu>Demos</guimenu><guisubmenu>Solution Moves</"
"guisubmenu> </menuchoice> (the <guimenuitem>Info</guimenuitem> item and "
"demonstrations of moves)."
msgstr ""
"Ne. Vendar pa je bila <trademark>Rubikova kocka</trademark> 3x3x3 obsežno "
"analizirana in metode rešitve lahko najdete na internetu in v elementu "
"menija <menuchoice><guimenu>Demos</guimenu><guisubmenu>Premiki rešitve</"
"guisubmenu> </menuchoice> (postavka <guimenuitem>Informacije</guimenuitem> "
"in predstavitve premikov)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:775
#, no-c-format
msgid "I have to quit the game now. Can I save my position?"
msgstr "Zdaj moram zapustiti igro. Ali lahko shranim svoj položaj?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:777
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Yes. In fact your position is saved automatically when you quit, just as "
"when you put a real cube back on the shelf. You can also save a particular "
"position by using menu item <menuchoice><guimenu>Game</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Save Puzzle…</guimenuitem></menuchoice> and the corresponding "
"shortcut keys and toolbar button."
msgstr ""
"Da. Pravzaprav se vaš položaj samodejno shrani, ko odstopite, tako kot "
"takrat, ko postavite pravo kocko nazaj na polico. Določen položaj lahko "
"shranite tudi z menijsko postavko <menuchoice><guimenu>Igra</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Shrani sestavljanko...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> ter "
"ustreznimi tipkami za bližnjice in gumbom v orodni vrstici."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:785
#, no-c-format
msgid "How do I restore the game I saved?"
msgstr "Kako obnovim igro, ki sem jo shranil?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:786
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Your automatically saved game is restored automatically when you start "
"&kubrick;. To load other saved games, use <menuchoice><guimenu>Game </"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Load Puzzle…</guimenuitem></menuchoice> and the "
"corresponding shortcut keys and toolbar button."
msgstr ""
"Vaša samodejno shranjena igra se samodejno obnovi, ko zaženete &kubrick;. Če "
"želite naložiti druge shranjene igre, uporabite <menuchoice><guimenu>Igra </"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Naloži sestavljanko...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> in "
"ustrezne tipke bližnjic ter gumb orodne vrstice."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:793
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where are the high scores?"
msgstr "Kje so visoki rezultati?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:794
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kubrick; does not have such a feature."
msgstr "&kubrick; nima take funkcije."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:801
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Configuration"
msgstr "Konfiguracija igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:803
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To open a configuration (settings) dialog use one of the menubar items: "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>&kubrick; Game Settings…"
"</guimenuitem></menuchoice> or <menuchoice><guimenu>Game</guimenu> "
"<guisubmenu>Choose Puzzle Type</guisubmenu></menuchoice> with the "
"<guimenuitem>Make Your Own…</guimenuitem> option at the end, which will "
"display a dialog with options to change cube dimensions and shuffling "
"difficulty. Below is a list of the options available."
msgstr ""
"Če želite odpreti pogovorno okno konfiguracije (nastavitev), uporabite enega "
"od elementov menijske vrstice: <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>&kubrick; Nastavitve igre ...</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> ali <menuchoice><guimenu>Igra</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Izberite "
"vrsto uganke</guisubmenu></menuchoice> z <guimenuitem>Naredite svojo... </"
"guimenuitem> na koncu, ki prikaže pogovorno okno z možnostmi za spreminjanje "
"dimenzij kocke in težavnosti mešanja. Spodaj je seznam razpoložljivih "
"možnosti."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:813
#, no-c-format
msgid "Watch shuffling in progress?"
msgstr "Oglejte si mešanje, ki poteka?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:814
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Provides an animated view of the cube when it is being shuffled by "
"the &kubrick; program.</action> You can select the speed of animation."
msgstr ""
"<action>Zagotavlja animirani pogled na kocko, ko jo &kubrick; program.</"
"action> Izberete lahko hitrost animacije."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:819
#, no-c-format
msgid "Watch your moves in progress?"
msgstr "Opazujte svoje poteze v teku?"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:820
#, no-c-format
msgid "Provides an animated view of your own moves at a speed you can select."
msgstr ""
"Omogoča animirani pogled vaših lastnih potez s hitrostjo, ki jo lahko "
"izberete."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:824
#, no-c-format
msgid "Speed of moves:"
msgstr "Hitrost premikov:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:825
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Sets the speed at which animations go. </action> The range is 1 to "
"15 degrees of turn per animation frame."
msgstr ""
"<action>Nastavi hitrost, s katero potekajo animacije. </action> Razpon je od "
"1 do 15 stopinj zasuka na okvir animacije."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:829
#, no-c-format
msgid "% of bevel on edges of cubies:"
msgstr "% poševnine na robovih kock:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:830
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Sets the percentage of bevelled edge on each cubie, relative to the "
"size of the colored stickers.</action> It affects the overall shape of each "
"cubie. The range is from 4% to 30%."
msgstr ""
"<action>Nastavi odstotek prirezanega roba na vsaki kocki glede na velikost "
"barvnih nalepk.</action> Vpliva na splošno obliko vsake kocke. Razpon je od "
"4 % do 30 %."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:835
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cube dimensions:"
msgstr "Dimenzije kocke:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:836
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Sets the three dimensions of the cube, brick or mat in cubies per "
"side.</action> Dimensions can range from 2x2x1 up to 6x6x6: the larger the "
"dimensions, the harder the puzzle. Only one of the dimensions can be 1, "
"otherwise the puzzle becomes too easy."
msgstr ""
"<action>Nastavi tri dimenzije kocke, opeke ali podloge v kockah na stran.</"
"action> Dimenzije lahko segajo od 2x2x1 do 6x6x6: večje kot so dimenzije, "
"težja je uganka. Samo ena od dimenzij je lahko 1, sicer uganka postane "
"prelahka."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:842
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moves per shuffle (difficulty):"
msgstr "Premikov na mešanje (težavnost):"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:843
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Sets the number of moves the &kubrick; program will use to shuffle "
"the cube.</action> The number can range from 0 to 50: the more moves, the "
"harder the puzzle. 2, 3 or 4 shuffling moves make for relatively easy "
"puzzles, especially if the shuffling moves can be watched."
msgstr ""
"<action>Nastavi število premikov &kubrick; program bo uporabil za "
"premešavanja kocke.</action> Število je lahko v razponu od 0 do 50: več "
"premikov, težja je uganka. 2, 3 ali 4 poteze mešanja omogočajo razmeroma "
"lahke uganke, še posebej, če lahko opazujete poteze mešanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:849
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Selecting zero moves can be useful if you wish to experiment with different "
"sequences of moves and what they do to the cube, such as when you are "
"searching for pretty patterns or new solving moves."
msgstr ""
"Izbiranje ničelnih potez je lahko koristno, če želite eksperimentirati z "
"različnimi zaporedji potez in s tem, kaj naredijo s kocko, na primer, ko "
"iščete lepe vzorce ali nove poteze za reševanje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:865
#, no-c-format
msgid "Credits and License"
msgstr "Zasluge in licenca"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:867
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kubrick; is Copyright 2008 Ian Wadham <email>ianw@netspace.net.au</email>"
msgstr ""
"&kubrick; je Copyright 2008 Ian Wadham <email>ianw@netspace.net.au</email>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kubrick; was inspired by Professor Ern&odblac; Rubik's famous "
"<trademark>Rubik's Cube </trademark> puzzle."
msgstr ""
"&kubrick; je navdihnil profesor Ern&odblac; Znana Rubikova uganka "
"<trademark>Rubikova kocka</trademark>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:876
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The programming is original work in C++ but owes several good ideas to the "
"Rubik XScreensaver, a C program by Marcelo Vianna, and GNUbik, a C program "
"by John M. Darrington."
msgstr ""
"Programiranje je izvirno delo v C++, vendar ima več dobrih zamisli Rubik "
"XScreensaver, program C Marcela Vianne, in GNUbik, program C Johna M. "
"Darringtona."

